</code></pre>
<p>The HTTP request does not execute this part of the script. Therefore, the table will remain empty.</p>
<p>How to enable the execution of scripts on the page is a separate issue. I suggest we consider a more direct solution.</p>
<pre class="lang-vb prettyprint-override"><code>Public Function GetFEDRates() As String
Dim objHTTP As Object
Dim URL As String
Dim result As String
Dim rows() As String
Dim dates() As String
Dim lowRates() As String
Dim highRates() As String
Dim tDate As Date, tLow As Double, tHigh As Double
Dim i As Integer
Dim decDelimiter As String
    URL = &quot;https://www.federalreserve.gov/aboutthefed/files/target-funds-2014-2024.csv&quot;
    Set objHTTP = CreateObject(&quot;Msxml2.XMLHTTP.6.0&quot;)
    objHTTP.Open &quot;GET&quot;, URL, False  ' async=false
    'objHTTP.setRequestHeader &quot;Content-type&quot;, &quot;text/csv&quot;
    'objHTTP.setRequestHeader &quot;Accept&quot;, &quot;application/json&quot;
    Call objHTTP.Send
    result = objHTTP.responseText
    Debug.Print &quot;Result:&quot;, result
    rows = Split(result, vbLf)
    For i = LBound(rows) To UBound(rows)
        Debug.Print &quot;row=&quot;, i
        Debug.Print rows(i)
    Next i
    decDelimiter = Mid(CStr(1.1), 2) ' only for locale delitimers like 1.2 or 1,2
    dates = Split(rows(0), &quot;,&quot;)
    lowRates = Split(rows(1), &quot;,&quot;)
    highRates = Split(rows(2), &quot;,&quot;)
    For i = LBound(dates) To UBound(dates)
        tDate = CDate(Left(dates(i), 10))
        tLow = CDbl(Replace(lowRates(i), &quot;.&quot;, decDelimiter))
        tHigh = CDbl(Replace(highRates(i), &quot;.&quot;, decDelimiter))
        Debug.Print &quot;Date=&quot;, tDate, &quot;Low=&quot;, tLow, &quot;High=&quot;, tHigh
    Next i
    GetFEDRates=&quot;ok&quot;
    Set objHTTP = Nothing
End Function```
